\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 87. T. canescens} Willd., {\i  Sp. Pl.}{\b  3}: 1369 (1802). Caespitose perennial; stems 10-30 cm, ascending, simple, clothed with appressed, white hairs. Stipules 20-30 mm, lanceolate, membranous below, herbaceous above. Leaflets of lower leaves 15-30 mm, thin, broadly oblong, deeply emarginate. Heads terminal, solitary, ovoid, lax. Calyx appressed-hairy; teeth 1-veined, the lowest only a little longer than the others and scarcely longer than the tube. Corolla c. 20 mm, creamy-white; standard twice as long as the calyx, emarginate.{\i   Mountain grassland. Krym.} Rs (K).
