\pard\f0\fs28  {\b T. constantinopolitanum} Ser. in DC.,{\i   Prodr. }{\b 2}: 193 (1825), is a plant of doubtful identity and affinity, variously treated as identical with or as a variety of{\b  88}, or as a subspecies of {\b 90}. Plants from Bulgaria, N. Greece and Turkey-in-Europe so treated are said to have stems with patent hairs, obovate leaflets, calyx-tube somewhat constricted at the apex, the lowest calyx-tooth scarcely longer than the tube, and corolla pale yellow. The legume is included in the calyx-tube as in {\b 90} and not exserted as in {\b 88}.
